        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "### Comparison with the Irving–Williams series\n\nThe classic Irving–Williams series predicts:\n\n> **Mn²⁺ < Fe²⁺ < Co²⁺ < Ni²⁺ < Cu²⁺ > Zn²⁺**\n\nThe SRD-46 ammonia data **largely conform** to this expectation:\n\n| Feature | Irving–Williams prediction | SRD-46 result | Match? |\n|---------|---------------------------|---------------|--------|\n| Monotonic rise Mn → Cu | Mn < Fe < Co < Ni < Cu | ✔ Observed exactly | ✅ |\n| Cu²⁺ is the strongest | Cu²⁺ at the top | log β₁ = 4.31, well above all others | ✅ |\n| Zn²⁺ drops below Cu²⁺ | Cu > Zn | 4.31 ≫ 2.37 | ✅ |\n| Zn²⁺ below Ni²⁺ | Ni > Zn | 2.81 > 2.37 | ✅ |\n| Zn²⁺ relative to Co²⁺ | Often Co < Zn or Co ≈ Zn | 2.11 < 2.37 (Zn slightly above Co) | ⚠️ Minor deviation |",
